{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-ba25131bef64d50a", "type": "tool_result", "content": "t) and 63.58% mAP on AV-Deepfake1M (+14.32% improvement), with 6x faster inference. Our frequency-domain analysis provides theoretical justification from a signal processing perspective for why skip-scanning inherently improves both accuracy and robustness.", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "35244b78-2bfd-4434-a5a0-193d888571d4", "uuid": "ac48f12d-72ee-4d06-afaa-f4d2cf6358dd", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T07:52:31.942Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "t) and 63.58% mAP on AV-Deepfake1M (+14.32% improvement), with 6x faster inference. Our frequency-domain analysis provides theoretical justification from a signal processing perspective for why skip-scanning inherently improves both accuracy and robustness.", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bab3a537395cfeff", "type": "tool_result", "content": "TITLE: Title: Audio-Visual Deepfake Detection With Local Temporal Inconsistencies\nABS: Abstract: This paper proposes an audio-visual deepfake detection approach that aims to capture fine-grained temporal inconsistencies between audio and visual modalities. To achieve this, both architectural and data synthesis strategies are introduced. From an architectural perspective, a temporal distance map, coupled with an attention mechanism, is designed to capture these inconsistencies while minimizing the impact of irrelevant temporal subsequences. Moreover, we explore novel pseudo-fake generation techniques to synthesize local inconsistencies. Our approach is evaluated against state-of-the-art methods using the DFDC and FakeAVCeleb datasets, demonstrating its effectiveness in detecting audio-visual deepfakes.", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "35244b78-2bfd-4434-a5a0-193d888571d4", "uuid": "66b090bf-9f03-44ed-b532-4fb5c26d633e", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T07:52:32.378Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "TITLE: Title: Audio-Visual Deepfake Detection With Local Temporal Inconsistencies\nABS: Abstract: This paper proposes an audio-visual deepfake detection approach that aims to capture fine-grained temporal inconsistencies between audio and visual modalities. To achieve this, both architectural and data synthesis strategies are introduced. From an architectural perspective, a temporal distance map, coupled with an attention mechanism, is designed to capture these inconsistencies while minimizing the impact of irrelevant temporal subsequences. Moreover, we explore novel pseudo-fake generation techniques to synthesize local inconsistencies. Our approach is evaluated against state-of-the-art methods using the DFDC and FakeAVCeleb datasets, demonstrating its effectiveness in detecting audio-visual deepfakes.", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1783410776505", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "我已经有足够的证据了。关键事实如下：\n- **UniSkip-Mamba (arXiv:2607.04498v1, 2026-07-05, 同期发表, 作者相同)** 在 LAV-DF 上报告了 AP@0.95 为 63.4%，在 AV-Deepfake1M 上报告了 63.58% mAP —— 这些数值远低于 EVAS 声称的 88.63% 和 70.20%。这种差异值得注意，但它是同期发表的工作。\n- 论文中引用了真实的 SOTA 基准（UMMAFormer, DiMoDif, MFMS, TriDet, ActionFormer）。\n- 已知的数据集：LAV-DF, AV-Deepfake1M, TVIL —— 这些是该领域真实的、已确立的基准。\n- 未提及代码发布 / GitHub 链接；摘要中声称“端到端”但在内文中表述不一致。\n\n让我快速验证一下 ablation 逻辑是否自洽。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "35244b78-2bfd-4434-a5a0-193d888571d4", "uuid": "460e0c8d-c4c1-4a02-bc4e-9e2ea63e1364"}
